Now I have a clear picture. Let me summarize my findings:

**Race on 2015-11-29**: Abu Dhabi Grand Prix (raceId 945), 55 laps total.

**Key data points:**
- 20 drivers started the race
- 19 drivers were still on track at lap 50 (all except Maldonado who retired with a collision on lap 0)
- All 19 of those drivers completed the race (though some were lapped)
- **11 drivers** have a `time` record in results (i.e., "finished" per the hint)
- 8 other drivers completed the race but were lapped (+1 to +3 laps behind), with no `time` record

**Analysis of the claim:**
